        <selectionEntry id="aa29-e384-3f5f-4742" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Softskin Transport (STAT CARD ON BACK)" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="243c-d108-b40a-e51f" name="Softskin Transport (STAT CARD ON BACK)" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">While the Panzer divisions have individual trucks for each Panzergrenadier section and a car for the platoon leader, Panzergrenadier divisions have fewer bigger trucks with the leader riding with the troops.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">This Infantry or Gun Unit may add a Softskin Transport Attachment. The number of vehicles in the Unit is as follows:
•	Add one Softskin Transport for every two Infantry Teams in the Unit.
•	Add one Softskin Transport for each Gun Team in the Unit.
The characteristics of an Softskin Transport are shown on the back of this card.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Infantry or Gun)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <categoryLinks>
        <categoryLink id="347e-27ec-6bc9-f573" name="New CategoryLink" hidden="false" targetId="c5b6-63ee-3f81-25f2" primary="true"/>
      </categoryLinks>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="1.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="ec0b-8424-c19d-625d" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Mobelwagen AA Tanks (STATS ON CARD)" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="5a09-5876-2575-287b" name="Mobelwagen AA Tanks" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">The Mobelwagen (furniture van) anti-aircrat tank is based on the Panzer IV chassis and its armed with a 3.7cm gun. With Allied air power increasingly dominating the battlefield, the anti aircraft platoon is essential for defense.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">This Unit has the following ratings and characteristics: (STATS ON CARD)</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Battle Group Ostwind AA Tank Platoon)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <categoryLinks>
        <categoryLink id="af19-7157-5d45-c5c6" name="New CategoryLink" hidden="false" targetId="c5b6-63ee-3f81-25f2" primary="true"/>
      </categoryLinks>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="-1.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="6590-0cca-d908-0b78" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Panzer Pioneer Platoon" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="d286-69be-a0c8-1f05" name="Panzer Pioneer Platoon" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Every panzer division had pioneers whose role was to clear the way for assaults, breaching minefields and clearing other obstacles.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Infantry Teams in this Unit cross Minefields safely on a roll of 2+.
This Unit Digs In on a roll of 3+.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Clausewitz Armoured Panzergrenadier Platoon), Limited</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <categoryLinks>
        <categoryLink id="a2c2-7421-be12-59b2" name="New CategoryLink" hidden="false" targetId="c5b6-63ee-3f81-25f2" primary="true"/>
      </categoryLinks>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="1.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="51e3-9fa5-6836-19d7" name="(CC) Panzer Lehrer" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="4c78-563c-d4bd-dcd2" name="0. Panzer Lehrer" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">When the replacement battalions were called into battle, training school teachers led their classes into battle.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Before Deploying this Unit, roll a die and give this Formation Commander the following command card at no additional point cost:
1 – Clever Hans
2 – Deadly Gunner
3 – Rapid Fire
4 – Schnell!
5 – Roll Over Them
6 – Choose one of the above.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Unit (Heavy Tank Training Company HQ, Tank Training Company HQ, Panzerdivision Muncheberg Tiger HQ)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile id="3a97-f21e-57ca-dad2" name="1. Clever Hans" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">It’s hard not to attract attention in a tank, but some tank commanders have the knack. Smooth movement and staying to low ground can make even the largest tank hard to spot.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">This Unit gains the Scout rule.
Scout: Teams remain Gone to Ground while Moving unless they Shoot or Assault.
*Use the Panzer Lehrer Skill card to get this card.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Panzer Lehrer Skill</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile id="8f81-e225-4287-f003" name="2. Deadly Gunner" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">With a deadly gunner in your Panzer, every shot hits exactly where it’s aimed.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">The Formation Commander may re-roll one failed Firepower Test during the Shooting Step.
*Use the Panzer Lehrer Skill card to get this card.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Panzer Lehrer Skill</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile id="c4e0-ee67-008c-4eb9" name="3. Rapid Fire" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">An ace gunner and an experienced loader allow a tank to engage and destroy numerous targets in a short span of time.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">The Formation Commander&apos;s tank has Halted ROF3 with its 8.8cm or 7.5cm gun.
*Use the Panzer Lehrer Skill card to get this card.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Panzer Lehrer Skill</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile id="7495-c308-b2b0-d7bc" name="4. Schnell" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Most of their kills have been racked up through being in the right place at the right time!</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">This Unit passes Blitz Move tests on 2+.
*Use the Panzer Lehrer Skill card to get this card.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Panzer Lehrer Skill</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile id="78a1-fd8f-2019-a09d" name="5. Roll Over Them" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">In a heavy tank, it’s easy. You just roll over them. Keep moving and there’s nothing they can do to stop you.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">This Unit Leader’s tank hits in Assaults on 2+.
*Use the Panzer Lehrer Skill card to get this card.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Panzer Lehrer Skill</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <categoryLinks>
        <categoryLink id="a94f-8a07-e5e7-a574" name="New CategoryLink" hidden="false" targetId="c5b6-63ee-3f81-25f2" primary="true"/>
      </categoryLinks>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="3.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="e800-e9cf-5e57-b78c" name=".BLG (CC) WIP 21cm Nebelwerfers (STATS ON CARD)" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="226d-2c8e-dfa1-ad3d" name="21cm Nebelwerfers" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">The 21cm NW42 rocket launcher batteries deliver crushing firepower at a moment’s notice. Their ability to bring a constant rain of fire upon advancing enemy infantry can break their assault in one volley.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">All 15cm Nebelwerfer Batteries in this Force have the following characteristics for +6 points for six Gun teams, or +3 points for three Gun teams:
Weapon: 21cm Nebelwerfer
Range: 72&quot;/180cm
ROF: SALVO
Anti-Tank: 2
Firepower: 3+</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (15cm Nebelwerfer Battery)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <categoryLinks>
        <categoryLink id="75a8-a426-8ca9-f76c" name="New CategoryLink" hidden="false" targetId="c5b6-63ee-3f81-25f2" primary="true"/>
      </categoryLinks>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="88ec-29ec-ddfa-f9fc" name=".BLG (CC) WIP 30cm Nebelwerfers (STATS ON CARD)" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="466c-e8b9-46a6-5e7c" name="30cm Nebelwerfers" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">The massive 30cm rockets used by the NW42 rocket launchers have a shorter range, but pack a powerful punch.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">All 15cm Nebelwerfer Batteries in this Force have the following characteristics for +6 points for six Gun teams, or +3 points for three Gun teams:
Weapon: 30cm Nebelwerfer
Range: 56&quot;/140cm
ROF: SALVO
Anti-Tank: 3
Firepower: 2+
Three Shots: 30cm Nebelwerfer Battery can only fire three Artillery Bombardments per game. Place three tokens next to the Unit, remove one each time it fires an Artillery Bombardment.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (15cm Nebelwerfer Battery)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <categoryLinks>
        <categoryLink id="c6bf-ab4b-35bb-0a5b" name="New CategoryLink" hidden="false" targetId="c5b6-63ee-3f81-25f2" primary="true"/>
        <categoryLink id="b49b-9b44-3849-02c1" name="New CategoryLink" hidden="false" targetId="c5b6-63ee-3f81-25f2" primary="false"/>
      </categoryLinks>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="2fa3-05ee-970d-e5c4" name=".BLG (CC) WIP 8.8cm Railway AA Gun" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="a076-289a-749a-bfce" name="8.8cm Railway AA Gun" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Flakregiment 122 had many of its guns mounted on railway flatcars, allowing them to be relocated as needed to hold off bombing raids. With the enemy striking into the heart of Germany these big guns have been pressed into service to help defend the Fatherland from enemy ground forces.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Field this Unit as a Luftwaffe 8.8cm Railway AA Platoon with the following characteristics:
Tactical: - , Terrain Dash: - , Cross Country: - , Road Dash: - , Cross: - 
Weapon: 8.8cm AA gun
Range: 40&quot;/100cm
Halted RoF: 2
Moving RoF: 1
Anti-Tank: 14
Firepower: 3+
Notes: Railway Gun (see command card), Self-defense AA

Both 8.8cm AA gun weapons can shoot each turn.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Luftwaffe 8.8cm Heavy AA Platoon), Limited</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <categoryLinks>
        <categoryLink id="e761-c35d-5199-0e69" name="New CategoryLink" hidden="false" targetId="c5b6-63ee-3f81-25f2" primary="true"/>
      </categoryLinks>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="2.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="ac78-dc68-615e-13be" name="(CC) Lucky" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="81be-358b-c05f-c638" name="Lucky" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Some men have all the luck.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Discard this card to re-roll any one die. The second result must be used.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Force, Limited</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="1.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="6650-b9d0-a0e1-a535" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Goliath Remote Control Bomb" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="d0e7-1b99-7c3e-4bd5" name="Goliath Remote Control Bomb" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7"/>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">If the Unit Leader did not Move, discard this card to pick an enemy Infantry or Gun Team in Bulletproof Cover up to 12&quot;/30cm away from, and in Line of Sight of, the Unit Leader. Roll a Skill test for the Unit Leader instead of Shooting:
- If passed, the enemy Team is Hit with a Firepower 3+ weapon and their Unit is Pinned Down. Infantry and Gun Teams must re-roll successful saves.
If the line between the Unit Leader and the enemy Team crosses Terrain mor than 2&quot;/5cm from the enemy Team, roll a die for each item of terrain. Any roll that is not 4+ causes the attack to miss. If the line crosses any Impassible Terrain, the attack misses.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Unit, (Panzer Pioneer Platoon)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="2.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="1017-726d-54e3-f326" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Stuka zu Fuss" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="f07f-b998-9176-ed08" name="Stuka zu Fuss" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Sd Kfz 251 half-tracks in the third platoon of the Panzerpionierkompanie are fittedwith Wurfrahmen, frames for six huge 28cm rockets. These were so devastating that they were called Stuka zu Fuss - Stuka on foot.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Discard this card to fire a Stuka zu Fuss bombardment with all your SdKfz 251 half-tracks using the following weapon:
Weapon: 28cm rocket
Range: 36&quot;/90cm 
Halted/Moving ROF: SALVO
Anti-Tank: 3
Fire Power: 2+
Each Sd Kfz 251 half-track counts as one weapon firing.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Unit (Panzer Pioneer Platoon)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="4.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="05b1-6c00-6007-6f16" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Machine-Gun Nests" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="9cc1-92ca-3c3a-0b3c" name="Machine-Gun Nests" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">German infantry dug camouflaged nests for their heavy machine-guns, covering them with soil mounted over doors and beams stolen from wrcked houses.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">sMG34 or sMG42 HMG teams in this Unit cannot Move, but can rotate to face the target when Shooting, and are Nests.
Each HMG team is a separate Independent Team.
Nest: The Nests are always Concealed and in Bulletproof Cover.
Teams attacking a Nest must re-roll successful Firepower tests to Destroy it.
Nests cannot Charge into Contact.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Infantry)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="2.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="1f70-4a5b-1dbb-5e27" name=".BLG (CC) WIP &apos;Porsche&apos; Tiger II (Early) Tank" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="3556-be1d-c4e3-02ba" name="&apos;Porsche&apos; Tiger II (Early) Tank (STATS ON CARD)" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Two turret designs were used on the Tiger II. The initial design is sometimes called the &apos;Porsche&apos; turret due to the belief that Porsche designed it for their prototype. This turret is in face the initial Krupp design for both prototypes. These early models also had less armour and a number of mechanical issues.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">All Tiger II tanks in this unit have the following characteristics for -1 point per Tiger II:
(STATS ON CARD)</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Unit, (Tiger II Heavy Tank Training Company HQ, Tiger II Heavy Tank Training Platoon)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="09f9-cad2-4152-da9d" name="(CC) Kuno von Meyer" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="546d-b847-f802-134e" name="Kuno von Meyer" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Oberstleutnant Kuno von Meyer had already proved himself an inspiring and capable leader as a Panzer Abteilung commander with 116. Panzerdivision in France, and leading Panzer Regiment Coburg in the east, earning a Knight&apos;s Cross. Now he leads Panzer Regiment Muncheberg defending the eastern approaches to Berlin.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">When a Unit Leader is with 8&quot;/20cm and Line of Sight of this Formation Commander, the Unit passes Rally, Remount and Last Stand Tests on a 3+.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Unit, Warrior (Clausewitz Panther (IR) Tank Company HQ)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="5.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="2ce4-c1ac-8d26-fa1e" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Luch Scout Troop" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="b8fd-5842-45ef-a601" name="Luch Scout Troop" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Fully-tracked Panzerpah tanks are ideal for getting into places half-tracked and wheeled vehicles cannot go. The Panzer II L. Luchs (Lynx) has proven itself capable reconnaissance vehicle.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">You may take this Unit as a Luchs Scout Troop (LG139) using the points and characteristics from that Unit Card instead.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Unit (Sd Kfz 234 Heavy Scout Troop)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="1b41-5a8b-b678-9ffe" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Luch Scout Company" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="8ca7-a92f-88cd-a7ab" name="Luch Scout Company" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">By 1945 Panzeraufklarungsatbteilung 4 (4th Armoured Reconnaissance Battalion) of 4th Panzer Division was the only unit still fielding Panzer II Luchs light tanks as their heavy armoured cars.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Your Force includes one Luchs Scout Company, which is a Formation containing:
• 1	 HQ Unit of 1x Luchs (2cm) from (LG139) for 2 points.
• 3-8 Luchs Scout Troop (LG139)
• 0-1 Reconnaissance Platoon (LG174) 
		or Recconnaissance (Late) Platoon (LG399)</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Formation, Limited</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="4fce-e77d-49cc-6cb1" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Aufklarer 38(t) Scout Company" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="06fd-b598-0eb3-e9af" name="Aufklarer 38(t) Scout Company" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">The Aufklarer 38(t) served as the heavy armoured cars in the Panzeraufklarungabteilung &apos;Grossduetschland&apos; and Panzeraufklarungabteilung 3.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Your Force includes one Aufklarer38(t) Scout Company  which is a Formation containing:
• 1	 HQ Unit of 1x Aufklarer38(t) (2cm) from the Aufklarer38(t) Scout Troop (LG484) for 1 point.
• 3-8 Aufklarer38(t) Scout Troop (LG484)
• 0-1 Reconnaissance (Late) Platoon (LG399)</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Formation, Limited</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="1ae2-ad4c-e41a-1858" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Sd Kfz 234 Scout Company" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="9bb9-9682-8491-6475" name="Sd Kfz 234 Scout Company" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">The final organisations of the heavy armoured car company of the Panzeraufklarungsabteilung (armoured reconnaissance battalion) had four platoons, each broken into three troops of two Sd Kfz 234, consisting of once Sd Kfz 234/1 (2cm) and either a Sd Kfz 234/3 (7.5cm) or a Sd Kfz 234/4 (7.5cm PaK40) for heavy fire support.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Your Force includes one Sd Kfz 234 Scout Company, which is a Formation containing:
• 1	 HQ Unit of 1x Sd Kfz 234 (2cm) armoured car from (LG482) for 1 points.
• 4-8 Sd Kfz 234 Heavy Scout Troop (LG482)
• 0-1 Reconnaissance Platoon (LG174)</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Formation, Limited</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="4658-73ee-2e4a-1785" name=".BLG (CC) WIP 10.5cm leFH 18/40 Howitzer (STATS ON CARD)" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="3a44-6d69-429b-ef7e" name="10.5cm leFH 18/40 Howitzer" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">The 10.5cm leFH 18/40 howitzer is the lightened version of the standard German field howitzer. It uses the light carriage of the 7.5cm PaK40 anti-tank gun, as well as wheels of lighter contruction, but with a bigger muzzle brake to reduce recoil. The new design saves materials for the war effort and makes it easier to manhandle for its crews.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">All 10.5cm howitzers in this Unit have the following characteristics: (STATS ON CARD)</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Volks 10.5cm Artillery Battery, 10.5cm Artillery Battery)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="1.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="5e9e-0bc1-d284-1b2a" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Looted T-34 (STATS ON CARD)" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="aedf-4606-f86f-3c0d" name="Looted T-34" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Resourceful panzer regiments put captured tanks back into action when replacements are in short supply.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">You may field a Looted T-34 (76mm) tank for 3 points or a Looted T-34 (85mm) tank for 4 points from (LS122). This Tank is an Independent Tank Team with the following ratings:
(STATS ON CARD)
Independant: Team cannot Charge into Contact or take an Objective, and is ignored for Victory Points.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Tank), Limited</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="7edd-2262-33f3-c2a4" name="(CC) Horst Zobel" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="0205-5480-f7ae-fe3d" name="Horst Zobel" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Major Horst Zobel commanded Panzer-Abteilung Munchenberg, one of two tank battalions of Panzerdivision Muncheberg. He was awarded his Knight&apos;s Cross for actions at the Seelow Heights, east of Berlin where his unit destroyed 59 Soviet tanks without a single German tank lost.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">When a Unit Leader is within 6&quot;/15cm and Line of Sight of the Formation Commander, the Unit passes Tactics on a 2+.
One Tank team each turn within 6&quot;/15cm of this Formation Commander may reroll failed rolls To Hit Tank Teams.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Unit, Warrior (Panzer Battle Group HQ, Clausewitz Panther (IR) Tank Company HQ)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="5.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="dd22-0116-2ffb-d4cb" name="(CC) Hans-Ulrich Rudel" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="496e-6542-5d4e-9c69" name="Hans-Ulrich Rudel" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Oberst Hans-Ulrich Rudel flew 2530 combat missions claiming at least 2000 targets destroyed. These included 800 vehicles, 519 tanks, 150 artillery pieces, 70 landing craft, nine aircraft, four armoured trains, several key bridges, a destroyer, two cruisers, and the Soviet battleship Marat.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">This Aircraft Unit arrives on a roll of 3+ (instead of 4+).
The Unit Leader may re-roll all failed rolls To Hit each time he Shoots with his 3.7cm gun.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Unit, Warrior (Ju 87 Stuka (3.7cm) Tank-hunter Flight)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="6.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="4c13-6f0a-e980-e91d" name=".BLG (CC) WIP SS-Panzerbrigade Westfalen Battle Group" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="c5b4-998b-b579-0b93" name="SS-Panzerbrigade Westfalen Battle Group" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">SS-Panzerbrigade Westfalen stood firm at a time where other German forces quit the field. Their steadfast defence of Paderborn forced the Allies to commit to a major attack to deal with them.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Your Force includes one SS-Panzerbrigade Westfalen Battle Groupy, which is a Formation containing:
• 1	 HQ Unit of 2x StG44 assault rifle team from and using the card special rules of the Berlin Battle Group HQ (LG527) for 4 points.
• 2-3 SS Grenadier Platoon *see command card*
• 0-1 sMG42 SS Machine-gun Platoon (LG209)
• 0-1 8cm SS Mortar Platoon (LG210) 
• 0-1 SS Scout Platoon *see command card*
• 0-1 SS Tank-hunting Platoon *see command card*</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Formation, Limited, Title</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="2354-bb29-044d-bb8e" name=".BLG (CC) WIP SS-Panzerbrigade Westfalen SS Grenadier Platoon" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="5dd5-96be-95d0-b706" name="SS-Panzerbrigade Westfalen SS Grenadier Platoon" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">SS-Panzerbrigade Westfalen served as the linchpin of the German defence of the Paderborn area. The brigade was commanded by SS-Obersturmbannfuhrer Hans Stern and fielded two regiments. The unit was a motley collection of training and convalescent forces supported by heavy armour and various infantry formations.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">This Unit replaces the MG42 team weapon with MG42 &amp; K98 rifle team weapon for -1 point per unit.
Weapon: MG42 &amp; K98 rifle team
Range: 16&quot;/40cm
RoF Halted: 2
RoF Moving: 1
Anti-Tank: 2
Firepower: 6</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Ardennes SS Panzergrenadier Platoon), Title</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="cb85-c9b2-e9c4-89e2" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Volkssturm Machine-Gun Platoon" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="eda9-b759-fb3e-2b6e" name="Volkssturm Machine-Gun Platoon" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">The Siemens Company in Berlin formed the best trained and most well-equipped Volksturm battalion to take part in the battle. This battalion was led by WWI veteran officers and equipped with a good selection of weapons, including machine-guns.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">This Unit loses Third Reich, gains Local Militia (see Volkssturm Platoon) and has the following ratings for: 
4x sMG34 HMG team		2 points
Motivation: 5+
Last Stand 6
Skill: 5+
Assault 6
Is Hit On: 3+</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (sMG34 Machine-gun Platoon), Title</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="eb5d-ce8e-4079-64e1" name=".BLG (CC) WIP 10.5cm AA Gun" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="921d-e6ae-d7ea-9ecf" name="10.5cm AA Gun" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">The Luftwaffe Flak Korps are trained in anti-aircraft work, but have little or no expertise in ground combat. They are normally kept behind the German front line, but as the Soviets rapidly advance they keep finding themselves in the thick of the battle. Heavy AA guns like the 10.5cm FlaK39 were soon proving themselves capable anti-tank weapons.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Field this Unit as a Luftwaffe 10.5cm Heavy AA Platoon with the following Characteristics:
Weapon: 10.5cm AA gun
Range: 48&quot;/120cm 
Halted RoF: 1
Moving RoF: 1
Anti-Tank: 19
Firepower: 2+
Notes: Self-defence AA, Slow Firing</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Luftwaffe 8.8cm Heavy AA Platoon), Limited</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="1.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="8fd8-d686-0c92-fef8" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Long 8.8cm AA Gun" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="39b1-fef5-f1cb-3ef4" name="Long 8.8cm AA Gun" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">The Luftwaffe Flak Korps also had a few rare 8.8cm FlaK41 anti-aircraft guns. These were developed to target high-flying aircraft, and though developed for a different task proved just as good as the army&apos;s 8.8cm PaK43 against armoured ground targets.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Field this Unit as a Luftwaffe Long 8.8cm Heavy AA Platoon with the following characteristics at +2 points for two Gun teams or +3 points for four Gun teams:
Weapon: Long 8.8cm AA gun
Range: 48&quot;/120cm
Halted RoF: 2
Moving RoF: 1
Anti-Tank: 17
Firepower: 3+
Notes: Self-defence AA</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Luftwaffe 8.8cm Heavy AA Platoon), Limited</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="8b39-83e9-9a34-7ef2" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Sniper School" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="8712-89f4-80df-0b72" name="Sniper School" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">As different Ausbildungs (training) forces were assembled from various training schools the infantry units available to the battle groups could range from raw cadets to specialists undergoing further training.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">All MG42 teams in this Unit become K98 rifle teams, retaining the Panzerfaust. They cannot take Sd Kfz 251 half-track transports and have the following characteristics for -2 points. 
Weapon: K98 rifle team
Range: 16&quot;/40cm
Halted RoF: 1
Moving RoF: 1
Anti-Tank: 2
Firepower: 6
Notes: Slow Firing
Snipers: If Pinned Down, Teams in this Unit do not suffer the normal +1 penalty To Hit for Slow Firing.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Panzergrenadier Training Platoon)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="d596-c2ae-e3ee-790c" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Railway Guns" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="a7dd-fbab-943e-37fc" name="Railway Guns" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Railway guns are mounted on railway flat cars and are set-up in a position to cover it with anti-aircraft fire. Railway FlaK-Regiments are not tactically mobile and are usually moved into position sometime before the battle.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">A Railway Gun Unit is always placed from Ambush in addition to any Units allowed by the mission. Each Team must be paced within 1&quot;/2.5cm of another Railway Gun Team and is always In Command.
During deployment place a straight length of railway connecting a table edge in your deployment area to a different table edge. Railway Gun Units must be placed from Ambush as if Concealed along this railway line within their deployment area. A Railway Gun Unit cannot be a carried or towed as Passengers.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Unit (any Railway AA Gun Unit)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="1c3e-c113-e2df-2801" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Pioneer School" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="a093-0e5f-4b70-5576" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Pioneer School" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">As different Ausbildungs (training) forces were assembled from various training schools the infantry units available to the battle groups could range from raw cadets to specialists undergoing further training.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Infantry Teams in the Unit cross Minefields safely on a roll of 4+</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Panzergrenadier Training Platoon)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="1.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="e8a2-9923-f515-56ce" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Panzerdivision Muncheberg Tiger HQ" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="8c9b-d814-9ebc-bdf0" name="Panzerdivision Muncheberg Tiger HQ" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Panzerdivision Muncheberg had a company of 13 Tiger tanks it fielded as part of its 1st battalion.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">This Unit is 1x Tiger for 8 points using the ratings and characteristics from the Clausewitz Tiger Tank Platoon (LG481).</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Panther (Late) Panzer Battle Group HQ), Limited, Title</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="dd95-8a39-d918-f684" name=".BLG (CC) WIP 1st &amp; 2nd Marine-Grenadier Division Kiegsmarine" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="3850-9ae6-b64c-86ae" name="1st &amp; 2nd Marine-Grenadier Division Kiegsmarine" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">The Marine-Grenadier divisions were made up of men from the German Navy (Kriegsmarine).</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Your Force includes a Marine-Grenadier Company which is a Formation containing:
• 1	 Marine-Grenadier Company HQ
• 1-2 Marine-Grenadier Assault Platoon
• 1	 Marine-Grenadier Rifle Platoon
• 0-1 Marine-Grenadier sMG42 Machine-gun Platoon
• 0-1 Marine-Grenadier 8cm Mortar Platoon
• 0-1 Marine-Grenadier 15cm Gun Platoon 
	 or Marine-Grenadier 12cm Mortar Platoon
• 0-1 Marine-Grenadier Tank-hunting Platoon 
	 or Marine-Grenadier 7.5cm Tank-hunter Platoon
See 1st &amp; 2nd Marine-Grenadier Divisions command cards for Unit builds.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Formation, Title</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="3345-91a1-5f45-488e" name="(CC) Gustav Walle" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="2f8d-3b01-544c-442d" name="Gustav Walle" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Major Gustav Walle, joined by Leutnant Fritz Anding, and Obergefreiter Nepomuk Stutzle, equipped with a Kubelwagen full of Panzerfausts, distinguished themselves on the night of the 14/15 April 1945 where they destroyed over 20 British armoured vehicles with Panzerfausts.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Add this Unit to your Formation. This Unit has 2x StG44 assault rifle teams with Panzerfaust from Clausewitz Panzersturm Platoon. This Unit has the following ratings and each team rolls two dice in Assaults when using a Panzerfaust weapon. 
(STATS ON CARD)</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit, Warrior (any Clausewitz Formation)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="6.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="765c-cad5-0c8f-72b7" name=".BLG (CC) WIP SS-Panzerbrigade Westfalen SS Scout Platoon" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="5cb4-3859-3e35-dd9c" name="SS-Panzerbrigade Westfalen SS Scout Platoon" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Scout teams on foot brave enemy fire, often closing to within metres of the enemy, but they are able to obtain vital intelligence needed by the brigade to strike the enemy where it matters.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">This Unit replaces the MG42 team weapon with K98 rifle team weapon, gains Spearhead and Scout and has the following characteristics at no cost.
Weapon: K98 rifle team
Range: 16&quot;/40cm
RoF Halted: 1
RoF Moving: 1
Anti-Tank: 2
Firepower: 6
Notes: Slow firing
Motivation: 3+
Counterattack 5+
Skill: 4+
Assault 5+</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Ardennes SS Panzergrenadier Platoon), Title</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="289d-4680-afd8-99bc" name=".BLG (CC) WIP SS Tank-Hunting Platoon" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="8a8f-0e24-ce44-49fe" name="SS Tank-Hunting Platoon" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Many Waffen-SS battalions formed tank-hunting parties equipped with Panzerfaust and Panzerschreck.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Add an SS Tank-Hunting Platoon to this Formation. This Unit has the Ratings of an Ardennes SS Panzergrenadier Platoon (LG442) and the following Teams and Weapons.
4x K98 rifle team with Panzerfaust &amp;
3x Panzerschreck tank-hunter team
(Panzerschreck tank-hunter teams are based on a medium base with 2 gunners and 2 loaders. The Unit Leader is one of the K98 teams mounted on a small base)
Weapon: K98 rifle team	Range: 16&quot;/40cm		RoF: 1	Anti-Tank: 2		Firepower: 6
		or Panzerfaust	Range: 4&quot;/10cm		RoF: 1	Anti-Tank: 12		Firepower: 5+
Weapon: Panzerschreck	Range: 8&quot;/20cm		Halted RoF: 2 Moving RoF: 1	Anti-Tank: 11		Firepower: 5+
Notes: K98 rifle, Panzerfaust: Slow firing</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Formation (Berlin Battle Group)</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="5557-f506-4117-73e1" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Volkssturm Mortar Platoon" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="5cf2-be7e-28e4-651c" name="Volkssturm Mortar Platoon" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">The Siemensstadt (Seimens City) Volkssturm battalion also had mortars as part of its weapons company.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">This Unit loses Third Reich, gains Local Militia (see Volkssturm Platoon) and has the following ratings for: 
4x 8cm mortar	3 points
Motivation: 5+
Last Stand 6
Skill: 5+
Assault 6
Is Hit On: 3+</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (8cm Mortar Platoon), Title</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="6496-7217-5a67-835d" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Volkssturm Infantry Gun Platoon" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="fab0-e2be-5dbf-1216" name="Volkssturm Infantry Gun Platoon" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">The Siemensstadt Volkssturm battalion had prepared well and were even able to provide a company of infantry guns to help defend Berlin from the coming Red Army assault.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">This Unit loses Third Reich, gains Local Militia (see Volkssturm Platoon) and has the following ratings for: 
2x s7.5cm infantry gun		4 points
Motivation: 5+
Last Stand 6
Skill: 5+
Assault 6
Is Hit On: 3+</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (7.5cm Gun Platoon), Title</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="ec9b-54bc-5b13-d431" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Twin 3.7cm AA Gun" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="cbb6-b79a-98a0-e96b" name="Twin 3.7cm AA Gun" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">The Luftwaffe is responsible for defending German troops from enemy aircraft. To do this, they have stationed anti-aircraft batteries all along the front line and created flak strongpoints covering the most vital areas. The Luftwaffe has a variety of anti-aircraft guns available including the twin 3.7cm Flakzwilling 43.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Field this Unit as a Luftwaffe Twin 3.7cm AA Platoon with the following characteristics:
Weapon: Twin 3.7cm AA
Range: 24&quot;/60cm
Halted RoF: 4
Moving RoF: 2
Anti-Tank: 7
Firepower: 4+
Notes: Dedicated AA</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Luftwaffe 3.7cm AA Platoon), Limited</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="1.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="7c50-bf40-349b-1e1a" name=".BLG (CC) WIP Twin 8.8cm Railway AA Gun" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="a22e-6a7b-fe5b-e4c9" name="Twin 8.8cm Railway AA Gun" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Flakregiment 122 had many of its guns mounted on railway flat cars. Some of these fat cars were fitted with two 8.8cm FlaK37 guns with ammunition racks in the center of the car.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Field this Unit as a Luftwaffe Twin 8.8cm Railway AA Platoon with the following characteristics at +5 points per two Gun teams:
Tactical: - , Terrain Dash: - , Cross Country: - , Road Dash: - , Cross: - 
Weapon: 8.8cm AA gun
		 8.8cm AA gun
Range: 40&quot;/100cm
Halted RoF: 2
Moving RoF: 1
Anti-Tank: 14
Firepower: 3+
Notes: Railway Gun (see command card), Self-defense AA

Both 8.8cm AA gun weapons can shoot each turn.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Luftwaffe 8.8cm Heavy AA Platoon), Limited</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <categoryLinks>
        <categoryLink id="2fc2-b979-1b8c-9643" name="New CategoryLink" hidden="false" targetId="c5b6-63ee-3f81-25f2" primary="true"/>
      </categoryLinks>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="05f8-21fc-c006-8d1c" name=".BLG (CC) WIP 10.5cm Railway AA Gun" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="b2d5-1083-f74b-84eb" name="10.5cm Railway AA Gun" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Flakregiment 122 had many of its guns mounted on railway flatcars, allowing them to be relocated as needed to hold off bombing raids. With the enemy striking into the heart of Germany these big guns have been pressed into service to help defend the Fatherland from enemy ground forces.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Field this Unit as a Luftwaffe 10.5cm Railway AA Platoon with the following characteristics:
Tactical: - , Terrain Dash: - , Cross Country: - , Road Dash: - , Cross: - 
Weapon: 10.5cm AA gun
Range: 48&quot;/120cm
Halted RoF: 1
Moving RoF: 1
Anti-Tank: 19
Firepower: 2+
Notes: Railway Gun (see command card), Self-defense AA, Slow Firing

Both 8.8cm AA gun weapons can shoot each turn.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Luftwaffe 8.8cm Heavy AA Platoon), Limited</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <categoryLinks>
        <categoryLink id="e712-f841-9291-1e46" name="New CategoryLink" hidden="false" targetId="c5b6-63ee-3f81-25f2" primary="true"/>
      </categoryLinks>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="2.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="ad6c-7ab7-eaf3-f0fb" name=".BLG (CC) WIP 1st &amp; 2nd Marine-Grenadier Division Marine Infantry" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="b51c-ee0d-859e-a378" name="1st &amp; 2nd Marine-Grenadier Division Marine Infantry" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">The men from the Kriegsmarine were young and enthusiastic and willing to do their bit in defence of the Fatherland.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Use this card to build the Marine-Grenadier Company HQ, Marine-Grenadier Assault Platoon, and Marine-Grenadier Rifle Platoon.
These Units lose Third Reich, and have the following ratings for +2 points per Volksgrenadier Assault or Rifle Platoon, and +1 point per Volksgrenadier Company HQ Unit:
Motivation: 3+</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Bulge: German Volksgrenadier Company HQ, Volksgrenadier Assault Platoon, Volksgrenadier Rifle Platoon), Title</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="fb9d-4999-89f4-e406" name=".BLG (CC) WIP 1st &amp; 2nd Marine-Grenadier Division 7.5cm Anti-Tank" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="742b-10b8-899e-c7c6" name="1st &amp; 2nd Marine-Grenadier Division 7.5cm Anti-Tank" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Marine-Panzerjager-Abteilung 2 is armed with two companies of 7.5cm PaK40 anti-tank guns. These were allocated out to aid the defence of the division against British tanks.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Use this card to build the Marine-Grenadier 7.5cm Tank-hunter Platoon.
All Gun Units in this Formation lose Third Reigh, and have the following ratings for:
4x 7.cm gun		13 points
3x 7.cm gun		10 points
2x 7.cm gun		6 points
Motivation: 3+</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Bulge: German Volksgrenadier 7.5cm Tank-hunter Platoon), Title</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="2f30-82e1-aaf2-11df" name=".BLG (CC) WIP 1st &amp; 2nd Marine-Grenadier Division Artillery" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="9f73-8384-0ed9-c7d3" name="1st &amp; 2nd Marine-Grenadier Division Artillery" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Marine-Artillerie-Regiment 2 was unable to join the rest of the division until mid-April as it was stuck in Schleswig-Holstein while it waited for sufficient horses to mobilise it. Upon arrival, they were able to add their weight to the division&apos;s defensive positions. They were armed with a mix of German 10.5cm leFH18/40 and captured Soviet 12.2cm FH396(r) howitzers.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">This Unit loses Third Reich, and has the following ratings for +1 point per two guns:
Motivation: 3+</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Volks 10.5cm Artillery Battery), Title</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="17f5-d3e3-6bd7-273f" name=".BLG (CC) WIP 1st &amp; 2nd Marine-Grenadier Division 15cm Gun Platoon ***(STATS ON CARD)***" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="5378-d3c5-a81b-fd3d" name="1st &amp; 2nd Marine-Grenadier Division 15cm Gun Platoon" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7"/>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Use this card to build the Marine-Grenadier 15cm Gun Platoon. 
This Unit loses Third Reich, and has the following ratings for:
2x 15cm infantry gun		 6 points
Tactical: 2&quot;/5cm
Terrain Dash: 2&quot;/5cm
Cross Country: 4&quot;/10cm
Road Dash: 6&quot;/15cm
Cross: 5+
***(STATS ON CARD)***
Motivation: 3+
Notes: Brutal, Forward Firing, Slow Firing</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Bulge: German Volksgrenadier 7.5cm Gun Platoon), Title</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="6330-0605-e53f-91ab" name=".BLG (CC) WIP 1st &amp; 2nd Marine-Grenadier Division Hetzers" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="c68b-d9b4-9c6f-b1d8" name="1st &amp; 2nd Marine-Grenadier Division Hetzers" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Marine-Panzerjager-Abteilung 2 was also issued Hetzer tank-hunters. At least two of these supported the Fusilier battalion in the defence of the Essel Bridgehead against the British 45 (RM) Commando, though it seems the British may have mistaken them for Elefant tank-hunter tanks! Heers-Panzerjager-Abteilung 741 was also issued with Hetzer tank-hunters and supported 2. Marine-Grenadierdivisions.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">This Unit has the following ratings for +1 point per tHetzer:
Motivation: 3+
Counterattack 4+
Skill: 4+
Assault 5+</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Hetzer Tank-hunter Training Platoon), Title</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="2407-cb21-ba59-0efa" name=".BLG (CC) WIP 1st &amp; 2nd Marine-Grenadier Division Tank-Hunting Platoon (STATS ON CARD)" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="dc95-c389-de1d-388e" name="1st &amp; 2nd Marine-Grenadier Division Tank-hunting Platoon" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">The marines never had enough anti-tank guns, so formed tank-hunting parties equipped with Panzerfaust and Panzerschreck.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Use this card to build the Marine-Grenadier Tank-hunting Platoon. This Unit loses Third Reich, and has the following characteristics and ratings for:
4x K98 rifle team with Panzerfaust &amp;
3x Panzerschreck tank-hunter team 11 points
***(STATS ON CARD)***</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Bulge: German Volksgrenadier Rifle Platoon), Title</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="dcd5-71c5-2aa5-7b77" name=".BLG (CC) WIP 1st &amp; 2nd Marine-Grenadier Division Captured Guns (STATS ON CARD)" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="8f38-dd46-beac-6b54" name=".BLG (CC) WIP 1st &amp; 2nd Marine-Grenadier Division Captured Guns (STATS ON CARD)" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">Both Marine-Grenadier Divisions used captured artillery, the 1st fighting on the Oder Front used entirely captured guns, whiles the 2nd fighting in the west used a mix of captured Soviet 122mm howitzers and German 10.5cm howitzers.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">This Unit loses Third Reich, and has the following ratings and characteristics for +1 point per two guns:
***(STATS ON CARD)***</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Volks 10.5cm Artillery Battery), Title</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
        <selectionEntry id="d316-c474-7b8b-d4ca" name=".BLG (CC) WIP 1st &amp; 2nd Marine-Grenadier Division Marine Weapons" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <profiles>
        <profile id="ca94-5d53-fcc5-625f" name="1st &amp; 2nd Marine-Grenadier Division Marine Weapons" hidden="false" typeId="5cbd-556d-67b5-1bd9" typeName="Command Card">
          <characteristics>
            <characteristic name="Info" typeId="bd5c-655e-1889-6af7">The men from the Kriegsmarine were young and enthusiastic and willing to do their bit in defence of the Fatherland.</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Details" typeId="4091-e11a-c858-f46e">Use this card to build the Marine-Grenadier sMG42 Machine-gun Platoon, Marine-Grenadier 8cm Mortar Platoon, and Marine-Grenadier 12cm Mortar Platoon.
These Units lose Third Reich, and have the following ratings for +1 point per 2x 8cm mortar or 2x 12cm mortar, and +1 point per sMG42 Machine-gun Platoon Unit:
Motivation: 3+</characteristic>
            <characteristic name="Notes" typeId="75a6-20ee-1c76-640a">German, Build, Unit (Bulge: German Volksgrenadier sMG42 Machine-gun Platoon, Volksgrenadier 8cm Mortar Platoon, Volksgrenadier 12cm Mortar Platoon), Title</characteristic>
          </characteristics>
        </profile>
      </profiles>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="995a-4d67-6920-bfe4" value="0.0"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
